ðŸ›  Tech Stack
Category	Technology
Framework	React Native (Expo)
Language	TypeScript
Navigation	Expo Router v3 (File-based routing)
State Management	React Context API
Storage	AsyncStorage
UI Components	React Native Core Components
Date Handling	JavaScript Date API
Development	Expo CLI, Metro Bundler
ðŸ— Architecture
Design Patterns
Context + Provider Pattern - Global state management for transactions and budgets

Component Composition - Reusable UI components

Screen-Based Architecture - Separation of concerns between screens and business logic

Async Storage Layer - Persistent data with AsyncStorage

Data Flow
text
User Action â†’ Screen Component â†’ Context (Business Logic) â†’ AsyncStorage
                â†“                      â†“                          â†“
              UI Update â† State Update â† Data Persisted
Context Architectureâ€‹
text
TransactionContext
â”œâ”€â”€ State: transactions[]
â”œâ”€â”€ Actions: add, update, delete
â”œâ”€â”€ Helpers: getTotalIncome, getTotalExpenses
â””â”€â”€ Storage: AsyncStorage persistence

BudgetContext
â”œâ”€â”€ State: budgets[]
â”œâ”€â”€ Actions: add, update, delete
â”œâ”€â”€ Helpers: calculateSpent, getBudgetByCategory
â””â”€â”€ Storage: AsyncStorage persistence
ðŸš€ Getting Started
Prerequisites
Node.js (v16 or higher)

npm or yarn

Expo CLI (npm install -g expo-cli)

Android Studio (for Android) or Xcode (for iOS)

Installation
Clone the repository

bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/finance-tracker.git
cd finance-tracker
Install dependencies

bash
npm install
# or
yarn install
Install required Expo packages

bash
npx expo install @react-native-async-storage/async-storage
npx expo install @react-navigation/bottom-tabs
Start the development server

bash
npx expo start
Run on device/emulator

Press a for Android

Press i for iOS (macOS only)

Press w for web

Scan QR code with Expo Go app

Clear Cache (if needed)
bash
npx expo start -c
