ðŸ§  Core Concepts
1. Transaction Model
typescript
interface Transaction {
  id: string;                    // Unique identifier (timestamp)
  type: 'income' | 'expense';    // Transaction type
  amount: number;                // Transaction amount (â‚¹)
  category: string;              // Category name
  description: string;           // Brief description
  date: string;                  // ISO date string
  notes?: string;                // Optional additional notes
}
Example:

json
{
  "id": "1733717200000",
  "type": "expense",
  "amount": 250.50,
  "category": "Food",
  "description": "Lunch at restaurant",
  "date": "2025-12-09",
  "notes": "With friends"
}
2. Budget Model
typescript
interface Budget {
  id: string;                    // Unique identifier
  category: string;              // Category to budget
  amount: number;                // Budget limit (â‚¹)
  period: 'weekly' | 'monthly';  // Time period
  spent: number;                 // Auto-calculated spent amount
}
Budget Calculation Logic:

Weekly: Checks transactions from last 7 days

Monthly: Checks transactions from last 30 days

Auto-updates: Recalculates on every transaction change

Color Coding:

ðŸŸ¢ Green (0-80%): On track

ðŸŸ  Orange (80-100%): Approaching limit

ðŸ”´ Red (>100%): Over budget

3. Data Persistence
AsyncStorage Keys:

transactions - Array of Transaction objects

budgets - Array of Budget objects

Storage Operations:

typescript
// Save
await AsyncStorage.setItem('transactions', JSON.stringify(transactions));

// Load
const stored = await AsyncStorage.getItem('transactions');
const parsed = stored ? JSON.parse(stored) : [];

// Clear (More screen)
await AsyncStorage.removeItem('transactions');
await AsyncStorage.removeItem('budgets');
ðŸ“š API Reference
TransactionContext
typescript
const {
  transactions,           // Transaction[]
  addTransaction,         // (transaction: Omit<Transaction, 'id'>) => Promise<void>
  deleteTransaction,      // (id: string) => Promise<void>
  updateTransaction,      // (id: string, data: Omit<Transaction, 'id'>) => Promise<void>
  getTotalIncome,         // () => number
  getTotalExpenses,       // () => number
  getTransactionsByDateRange  // (start: string, end: string) => Transaction[]
} = useContext(TransactionContext);
BudgetContext
typescript
const {
  budgets,                // Budget[]
  addBudget,              // (budget: Omit<Budget, 'id' | 'spent'>) => Promise<void>
  deleteBudget,           // (id: string) => Promise<void>
  updateBudget,           // (id: string, data: Omit<Budget, 'id' | 'spent'>) => Promise<void>
  getBudgetByCategory,    // (category: string) => Budget | undefined
  calculateSpent          // (category: string, period: 'weekly' | 'monthly') => number
} = useContext(BudgetContext);
ðŸ’» Development
Available Scripts
bash
# Start development server
npm start

# Start with cache cleared
npm start -- -c

# Run on Android
npm run android

# Run on iOS
npm run ios

# Run on web
npm run web

# Build for production
eas build --platform android
eas build --platform ios
Code Styleâ€‹
TypeScript for type safety

Functional components with hooks

Async/await for asynchronous operations

StyleSheet.create for component styling

Context API for state management

Best Practices Followedâ€‹
âœ… Separation of concerns (screens vs. contexts)
âœ… Type safety with TypeScript interfaces
âœ… Error handling in async operations
âœ… Input validation before saving
âœ… Confirmation dialogs for destructive actions
âœ… Loading states for async operations
âœ… Responsive design with percentage-based widths

ðŸ§ª Testing
Manual Testing Checklist
Transactions:

 Add income transaction

 Add expense transaction

 Edit existing transaction

 Delete transaction with confirmation

 Filter transactions (All/Income/Expense)

 Verify balance calculations

Budgets:

 Create weekly budget

 Create monthly budget

 Delete budget

 Verify spent calculation

 Check color-coded progress bars

 Verify budget alerts on home screen

Data Persistence:

 Close and reopen app

 Verify transactions persist

 Verify budgets persist

 Test "Clear All Data"

ðŸ“¦ Deployment
Build for Production
bash
# Install EAS CLI
npm install -g eas-cli

# Login to Expo
eas login

# Configure project
eas build:configure

# Build APK (Android)
eas build --platform android --profile preview

# Build AAB (for Play Store)
eas build --platform android --profile production

# Build IPA (iOS - requires Apple Developer account)
eas build --platform ios --profile production
Environment Configuration
Create app.json with proper configuration:

json
{
  "expo": {
    "name": "Finance Tracker",
    "slug": "finance-tracker",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "orientation": "portrait",
    "icon": "./assets/icon.png",
    "splash": {
      "image": "./assets/splash.png",
      "resizeMode": "contain",
      "backgroundColor": "#6200ee"
    },
    "android": {
      "package": "com.yourcompany.financetracker"
    },
    "ios": {
      "bundleIdentifier": "com.yourcompany.financetracker"
    }
  }
}
